verbose_text: While the KEL antigen could be readily detected initially following transfusion into KEL, B6, or C3 KO mice, consistent with the possibility that C3 may actually regulate KEL antigen accessibility during the developing immune response, transfusion of KEL RBCs into B6 recipients actually resulted in decreased levels of detectable KEL antigen over time when compared to control KEL mice transfused with syngeneic KEL RBCs.
